President Obama issued a statement congratulating Pakistan on its 63rd anniversary of independence. He praised the contributions of Pakistani Americans to the United States and expressed his support for the people of Pakistan in the face of the recent devastating flooding. The President directed his administration to provide financial assistance, relief supplies, helicopters, rescue boats, and disaster management experts to assist Pakistan in its response to the crisis. He also called on the international community to increase their support and assistance. The President reaffirmed America's commitment to helping Pakistan recover and expressed his desire to work together with Pakistan and the international community to restore the nation's vitality.